y civil rights movement, in order to paint a full portrait of her life and impact. Drawing from Hansberry’s papers, speeches, and interviews, this book presents its subject as both a playwright and a political activist. It also reveals a new perspective on the roles of black women in mid-twentieth-century political movements.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAfrican American dramatistsy20th centuryvBiography. 0aAfrican American political activistsy20th centuryvBiography. 0aLesbian dramatistsy20th centuryvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Entertainment & Performing Arts.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2021z9783110753783oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishz978311075403208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030025833240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300258332423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300258332/original  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075403-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DADb2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021